Background Data on Incidence of Mumps in Scotland
-------------------------------------------------
[The following background data on mumps in Scotland has been extracted from
the GIDEON database by Dr. Steve Berger.]
Routine immunization was introduced in 1968. Routine immunization
(Measles-Mumps-Rubella triple vaccine) is given at age 12 months, and [a
booster at] 3 to 5 years. During 1990 to 2001, infant vaccine coverage ranged
from 85-92 percent.
Year / Cases
1989 / 3095
1990 / 833
1991 / 723
1992 / 601
1993 / 458
1994 / 546
1995 / 371
1996 / 368
1997 / 282
1998 / 251
1999 / 218
2000 / 196
2001 / 151
2002 / 156
2003 / 86 [January to June]
No cases of mumps *meningitis* were reported during 1999 through 2002.
--
Steve Berger
Geographic Medicine
Tel Aviv Medical Center
<mberger@post.tau.ac.il>
